##SLK STACK CONFIGURATION:

###1. Login on ELK Stack
-Go to `https://www.elastic.co/downloads/elasticsearch ` Free Trial -> Login with your credentials -> Security Option - Self Hosted and Severless option -> SIEM and Security Analisys-> Cloud Provider: `Amazon Web Services` #Because of the 14 days free trial

###2.0 Insatlling Agent on Windows Server:
- Inside the ELK go to `Integrations` -> Set up Active Directory Entity Analytics:

-Copy the clipBoard and past on Active Directory Server -> in the [y/n] select: [y] -> the message that will appear on the terminal will be: "Elastic Agent has been succesfully installed."
https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/windows-server-install.png?raw=true

- Now need to check on the Siem and will get the message:
https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/ELK-agent-setup.png

- Select: "Add the Integration"

###3.0 Collect Identities:
- Setup Active Directory Base DN as: activecompany.local
-Active Directory URL as: LDAP://ActiveCompanyDC.activecompany.local/Default naming context
- Active Directory User as:administrator
-Active Directory User Password: Chosen1#77
-Setup Active Directory Dataset as: all
-Setup Sync Interval as: 1h
-Setup Update Interval as: 15m
- And Mark the "Include empty groups"
https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/fleet-siem.png?raw=true
-Press "Confirm Data"


###4.0 Navigate inside the ELK SIEM and go to Assets -> Agents -> Agent Policies -> Create Agent Policie -> Select on 'activecompany' 
- Add those three Integration Policies: Elastic Defende - System - Windows
- Navigate throut the Elastic Defend integarion and go to 'Integration Policies'  -> Click on Elastic Defend -> Edit Integration and Set every Policy Settings on 'Detect' only.

https://github.com/AbnerStier/ELK-SIEM-VS-ATOMIC/blob/main/images/policy.png

###5.0 Adding Elastic Rules:
- Filters by "Data Source: Active Directory", "Windows" -> Install all
- Select 'Tags' -> Filters all Sources that are installed ->  Select All 1850 Rules -> Bulk Actions -> Enable



